  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Kali129-kilavi">itu "taṉṉuṭ kaiyā ṟeytiṭu kiḷavi" (iṟai. cūt. 30) yāṟ ṟalaivi āṟṟāḷāyiṉavāṟu tōḻi talaivaṟkuk kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en"></p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="Kali129">
                <l>tollūḻi taṭumāṟit tokalvēṇṭum paruvattāṟ</l>
                <l>palvayi ṉuyirellām paṭaittāṉkaṭ peyarppāṉpō </l>
                <l>lelluṟu teṟukatir maṭaṅkittaṉ katirmāya </l>
                <l>nallaṟa neṟiniṟīi yulakāṇṭa varacaṉpi </l>
                <l>ṉallatu malaintirun taṟaneṟi niṟukkallā </l>
                <l>melliyāṉ paruvampōṉ mayaṅkiru ṭalaivara </l>
                <l>vellaikku varampāya viṭumpaikūr maruṇmālai;</l>
                <l rend="space">pāytirai pāṭōvāp parappunīrp paṉikkaṭa</l>
                <l>ṟūvaṟat tuṟantaṉaṉ ṟuṟaivaṉeṉ ṟavaṉṟiṟa</l>
                <l>nōyteṟa vuḻappārka ṇimiḻtiyō vempōlak </l>
                <l>kātalcey takaṉṟārai yuṭaiyaiyō nī; </l>
                <l rend="space">maṉṟirum peṇṇai maṭalcē raṉṟi </l>
                <l>ṉaṉṟaṟai koṉṟaṉa ravareṉak kalaṅkiya </l>
                <l>veṉṟuya raṟintaṉai naraṟiyō vempōla </l>
                <l>viṉṟuṇaip pirintārai yuṭaiyaiyō nī;</l>
                <l rend="space">paṉiyiruḷ cūḻtarap paitalañ ciṟukuḻa </l>
                <l>liṉivari ṉuyarumaṟ paḻiyeṉak kalaṅkiya </l>
                <l>taṉiyava riṭumpaikaṇ ṭiṉaitiyō vempōla </l>
                <l>viṉiyacey takaṉṟārai yuṭaiyaiyō nī; </l>
                <l rend="space">eṉavāṅku, </l>
                <l>aḻintaya laṟinta vevva mēṟpaṭap </l>
                <l>perumpē tuṟutal kaḷaimati peruma </l>
                <l>varuntiya cellaṟīrat tiṟaṉaṟi yoruvaṉ </l>
                <l>maruntaṟai kōṭaliṟ koṭitē yāḻaniṉ </l>
                <l>ṉaruntiyōr neñca maḻintuka viṭiṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l corresp="3">When his rays vanish, curbing the scorching rays that have light,</l>
                <l corresp="2">like he who removes from [his] place the one who created all live in on many sides,</l>
                <l corresp="1">by seasons that need to gather, as the old aeon deteriorates, </l>
                <l corresp="7">on obscure evening full of sorrow that is the boundary of day </l>
                <l corresp="6">when diffuse darkness comes to pass like in the season of a soft one </l>
                <l corresp="5">that does not establish the path of virtue, being opposed(?), except </l>
                <l corresp="4">after a king who ruled the world, establishing the path of good virtue, </l>
                <l>Chilly sea with water in an expanse where the sound of the leaping waves does not stop, </l>
                <l>saying “so that [your] strength is severed he abandoned [you], the man from the ghat”, </l>
                <l>would you thus buzz before those who bear pain to scorch [them] on his account? </l>
                <l corresp="8-11">Do you like us have someone who departed after making love [to you]? </l>
                <l>O Aṉṟil bird that joins the fronds of the big palmyra tree by the cow shed,</l>
                <l>you who know of the misery of me who is upset that </l>
                <l>he has killed with one stroke what was good, would you call?</l>
                <l corresp="12-15">Do you like us have someone who parted from [his] sweet consort?</l>
                <l>Sorrowful little flute, when the chilly darkness spreads,</l>
                <l>would you be desperate, seeing the sorrow of those who are alone,</l>
                <l>upset that if [he] comes now blame will rise?</l>
                <l corresp="16-19">Do you like us have someone who departed after doing sweet things?</l>
                <l corresp="20">That is to say,</l>
                <l>Remove, o great man, [her] having great folly</l>
                <l>while trouble increases that is desolately known in the neighbourhood.</l>
                <l>If you let go of those who have absorbed you so that [their] hearts pine in desolation</l>
                <l>it is as cruel as someone [but] announcing a remedy,</l>
                <l corresp="21-25">knowing the matter so that the unhappiness suffered will end.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
